In React how can I get Button in a parent component to dispatch a function onClick in multiple child components?In React, you can use the onClick property on a button in a parent component and pass a callback function that will be called when the button is clicked. This callback function can then be passed as a prop to multiple child components, where it can be invoked when the child components' elements are clicked.Here's an example:Copy code// Parent component
function Parent() {
  const handleClick = () => {
    console.log('Button was clicked');
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
      <Child1 onClick={handleClick} />
      <Child2 onClick={handleClick} />
    </div>
  );
}

// Child component 1
function Child1({ onClick }) {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>Click me</button>;
}

// Child component 2
function Child2({ onClick }) {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>Click me</button>;
}
In this example, the handleClick function is defined in the parent component and is passed as a prop to each of the child components. When the buttons in the child components are clicked, the handleClick function will be invoked.Please note that in the child component, The button doesn't have onClick prop, it gets that property from onClick prop passed to it.2 / 2So in the following example how would I get a child component to dispatch the handleSave function when the <button> in the EditMenuContainer component has been clicked? 

